title: Website Analytics for All Pages in 2016
description: This dataset is a direct export from DC government's Google Analytics report for all pages on the?http://www.dc.gov?web portal. This shows the top most visited pages on DC.gov. It is identified by the part of the URL after the dc.gov domain path where users have visited.More information at?http://support.google.com

title: Summer Meals Sites
description: DC's youth 18 and under can receive reimbursement for free nutritious meals and snacks as part of the DC Free Summer Meals Program (FSMP). The program operates June through August, with meal times and dates varying by location.For further details on summer meal sites please visit the?DC Office of the State Superintendent of Education.

title: Website Analytics for Content Drilldown in 2016
description: This dataset is a direct export from DC government's Google Analytics report for content drilldown on the?http://www.dc.gov?web portal. The content drilldown shows activity at the folder level or sections of the DC.gov website. In many cases, this can be considered as the agency level. However, the DC.gov website is more than just agency sites so there will be cases of other sections shown here.More information at?http://support.google.com.

title: All Summer Events
description: Summer events that have occurred, or will be occurring, sponsored by the District's Summer Strong DC. For more information visit?http://summer.dc.gov.

title: 2013 Private Building Energy and Water Performance Benchmarking (Retired)
description: This layer was retired on October 18, 2017.The Clean and Affordable Energy Act of 2008 established that all private buildings over 50,000 gross square feet within the District of Columbia (DC), including multifamily residences, must annually measure and disclose their energy and water consumption to the District Department of the Environment (DDOE). Benchmarking is defined as tracking a building?s energy and water use and using a standard metric to compare the building?s performance against past performance and to its peers nationwide. These comparisons have been shown to drive energy efficiency upgrades and increase occupancy rates and property values. DC has chosen U.S. EPA?s free, industry-standard ENERGY STAR? Portfolio Manager? tool for benchmarking and reporting. DDOE is required to publicly disclose the ENERGY STAR? Benchmarking results for each privately owned building that is subject to the benchmarking law, beginning with the 2nd year of benchmarking data for that building. For more information, see ddoe.dc.gov/energybenchmarking.

title: 2014 Building Energy and Water Performance Benchmarking (Retired)
description: This layer was retired on October 18, 2017.The Clean and Affordable Energy Act of 2008 established that all private buildings over 50,000 gross square feet within the District of Columbia, including multifamily residences, must annually measure and disclose their energy and water consumption to the Department of Energy and Environment (DOEE). Benchmarking is defined as tracking a building?s energy and water use and using a standard metric to compare the building?s performance against past performance and to its peers nationwide. These comparisons have been shown to drive energy efficiency upgrades and increase occupancy rates and property values. The District of Columbia has chosen U.S. EPA?s free, industry-standard ENERGY STAR? Portfolio Manager? tool for benchmarking and reporting. DDOE is required to publicly disclose the ENERGY STAR? Benchmarking results for each publicly or privately owned building that is subject to the benchmarking law, beginning with the 2nd year of benchmarking data for that building. For more information, see?http://doee.dc.gov/energybenchmarking

title: Summer Events in Next 7 Days
description: Summer events that are scheduled to occur in the next 7 days where youth can participate. For more information visit?http://summer.dc.gov.

title: Website Analytics for Landing Pages in 2016
description: This dataset is a direct export from DC government's Google Analytics report for landing pages on the?http://www.dc.gov?web portal.?The landing page is the first page viewed during a session, or in other words, the entrance page to the portal. Landing pages can be considered the most popular points of entry as users navigate the DC.gov website.More information at?http://support.google.com.

title: Summer Crime Initiative Areas
description: Area boundaries for the MPD Summer Crime Initiative. The DC?Metropolitan Police Department (MPD)?and other partner agencies have identified these areas for improvement in social and public safety resources.
